body:
This happened again.  I switched to TRACE mode for a while and there was a ton of failures to receive metadata requests and discovery errors but the last relevant method I found was:

{"timestamp":"2020-07-01T05:35:10,969","level":"DEBUG","thread":"beaconchain-async-0","class":"PeerSync","message":"Request 200 blocks starting at 242041 from peer 16Uiu2HAmVKjTm3YePQgQLxm3fsfAUVgE58opRHZGDXRNLNsqvzBv","throwable":""}


We should have printed that the request was complete or failed after than but it never happened.  Looks like somehow the request is hanging forever and we're either not timing out or the timeout isn't cancelling the waiting future correctly.
